profile:
Load of Rubbish makes junk removal easy. We can remove "almost" anything from "almost" anywhere. From furniture to appliances, household items, we do it all. No removal is too big or too small, we remove anything from a single item to an entire home or office.

At Load of Rubbish, we’re not fans of mysteries, especially when it comes to prices. We believe that customers deserve to know what they will be paying ahead of time. That’s why we have always, and will always, provide pricing online, on the phone and in person. We won’t force you to book an appointment to get a price, and we will never use high pressure sales tactics. We are different, and we believe different is good.

profile:
Junk Works - Hamilton
Starting in 2005, our company's founders, Mike Andreacchi and Brian Reardon, knew there were customers looking for dependable junk hauling service to clear clutter and unwanted items from homes and businesses. The two long-time friends founded Junk King™ and established a business in their garage. Since then the company has grown rapidly, but the superior service and attention to detail that made them stand out has remained the same. Now we are bringing the exceptional service and green junk removal to Canada with Junk Works.

We continue to do things the old-fashioned way, one customer at a time. We offer fair, up-front pricing, call you 15 - 30 minutes ahead of every job, and sweep up after ourselves.

Furniture Removal
Television Disposal & Recycling

services:
Junk Works provides a full range of junk removal services to businesses across the country.
Junk Works offers same day service that includes ALL LABOUR, vehicle expenses, dumping and recycling fees.
Our prices are simply based on the amount of volume your items take up on our truck.
We guarantee to beat any written estimate.
Our trucks are 20% larger making us more affordable.
Junk Works is fully bonded and insured.
Junk Works operates six days a week.
We recycle and donate up to 60% of what we pick up.
Locally owned and operated.
